result.execSummary:
The defendant Stacy Marie Lange was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Stacy Marie Lange is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Stacy Marie Lange was found guilty of Possession of Cocaine/Coca, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Judge Richards for HWC, RPR: Drost, Clerk: Liddle. ADA:   Michael E. Nieskes   DF ATTY:  John A. Kucinski   DF:  Stacy Marie Lange appeared from jail. Case called at 11:29 a.m. Atty Kucinski filed Motion. ADA Nieskes makes request to deny the motion do to it being handwritten. Court will order motion to be dismissed. ADA Nieskes requesting Victor Bradley be sequestered. Atty Kucinski objects. Court will grant request to sequester witness. Court will now allow Victor Bradley to be present in the courtroom. State calls Victor Bradley to the stand. S/T Victor Bradley. ADA Nieskes directs. Court advises witness of his rights. Mr. Bradley pleads the fifth. Court dismisses Mr. Bradley and instructs him to be sequestered. State calls officer Nick Kruger to the stand. S/T Deputy Kruger employed with St Croix County Sheriff's Dept. ADA Nieskes directs. Deputy identifies defendant in the courtroom. State requests court to take judicial notice of case 10CF38. Court so takes judicial notice of 10CF38. Atty Kucinski cross directs Deputy Kruger. No further direct or witnesses by the State. State moves for bind over. Atty Kucinski objects. ADA Nieskes gives arguement. Court over ruling objection and finds probable cause has been proven and binds defendant over for trial. Arraignment to be set with Commissioner Heckmann.  hml
